cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.GR, cs.MG. 

The paper deals with geometric structures and their approximations, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The use of collapses to simplify the Rips complex also suggests a connection to algebraic topology and discrete structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the homotopy type of shapes, which is a topic in geometric topology (cs.GT). The use of balls and their intersections suggests a connection to computational geometry and topology (cs.GR). Finally, the paper deals with the conversion of a complex into a triangulation, which is a topic in computational geometry and topology (cs.MG).
